juniperUni.name: juniperUni

revisions.description: Product re-branding: changed UMC to SDX.
Replaced Unisphere names with Juniper names.
Added REFERENCE clauses to OBJECT-IDENTITY definitions.
The initial release of this management informaiton module.

juniperUni.contactinfo: Juniper Networks, Inc. Postal: 10 Technology Park Drive Westford, MA 01886-3146 USA Tel: +1 978 589 5800 E-mail: mib@Juniper.net
juniperUni.description: The SNMP Management Identifiers (SMI) for the Juniper Networks enterprise. This is the top-level registry for SNMP managed objects and other SNMP related information modules under the Juniper Networks/ Unisphere SNMP management enterprise object identifier.

juniperUniMibs.name: juniperUniMibs
juniperUniMibs.description: This is the root object identifier under which Juniper Networks/ Unisphere SNMP managed object (MIB) modules are defined.

juniperUniExperiment.name: juniperUniExperiment
juniperUniExperiment.description: This object identifier roots experimental MIBs, which are defined as: 1) IETF work-in-process MIBs which have not been assigned a permanent object identifier by the IANA. 2) Juniper work-in-process MIBs that have not achieved final production quality or field experience. NOTE: Support for MIBs under the juniperUniExperiment subtree is temporary and changes to objects may occur without notice.

juniperUniAdmin.name: juniperUniAdmin
juniperUniAdmin.description: This is reserved for administratively assigned object identifiers, i.e. those not associated with MIB objects. Examples include items such as chipset or ASIC identifiers.

juniAgentCapability.name: juniAgentCapability
juniAgentCapability.description: This provides a root object identifier under which AGENT-CAPABILITIES modules are assigned. Each product's agent's capabilities definitions appear in a collection of separate modules.

juniNetMgmtProducts.name: juniNetMgmtProducts
juniNetMgmtProducts.description: This provides a root object identifier for the definition of nodes pertaining to Juniper Networks' network management products. Examples include: SDX - Service Deployment System NMC - Network Management Center NMC-RX - E-series element manager
